{
  "texts": [
    "To address the computational challenges of enforcing precise activation, we develop Unit Deviation Sampling (UDS), which reduces the complexity from factorial to quadratic while maintaining effectiveness.",
    "Traditional backdoor attacks in machine learning often use static single triggers (Yang et al., 2021; Gu et al., 2017) that can be revealed by trigger inversion techniques (Liu et al., 2019 (Liu et al.,, 2022)).",
    "Recent work (Huang et al., 2023a) proposes composite triggers that require parts to appear in system prompts.",
    "However, this approach can not be applied to disable system prompts beyond, as the system prompt is out of the attack's control.",
    "Style and syntactic backdoors (Qi et al., 2021a,b), which rely on specific sentence styles or structures, are also vulnerable to scanning techniques that can easily detect these limited patterns."
  ]
}